The '''1972 Monaco Grand Prix''' was a [[Formula One]] motor race held at [[Circuit de Monaco|Monaco]] on May 14, 1972. It was race 4 of 12 in both the [[1972 World Championship of Drivers]] and the [[1972 International Cup for Formula One Manufacturers]]. The track was substantially modified from 1971, in the interest of safety. The pits were moved to the harbor front, between the chicane and Tabac, and a new chicane was placed near Tabac.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.f1fanatic.co.uk/2007/05/24/grand-prix-flashback-monaco-1972/ |title=Beltoise scores his only win – and BRM’s last – at Monaco |last=Collantine |first=Keith |date=24 May 2007 |website=F1Fanatic |access-date=15 February 2015}}</ref> [[Jean-Pierre Beltoise]]'s victory was the only one of his Formula One World Championship career, and the last for [[British Racing Motors|BRM]].
