{{Infobox Bilateral relations|Austrian–Macedonian|Austria|Macedonia}}

'''Austria – Macedonia relations''' refer to the [[bilateral relations]] between the [[Austria|Republic of Austria]] and the [[Republic of Macedonia]].<ref name=mia>[http://www.mia.com.mk/default.aspx?mId=1&vId=70912687&lId=2&title=MACEDONIA+-+INTERNAL+AFFAIRS+ Macedonian Information Agency] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323052047/http://www.mia.com.mk/default.aspx?mId=1&vId=70912687&lId=2&title=MACEDONIA+-+INTERNAL+AFFAIRS+ |date=2012-03-23 }} PM Gruevski meets Austrian FM Spindelegger {{en icon}}</ref> Diplomatic relations between the two countries were established on 23 December 1994.<ref>[http://www.mfa.gov.mk/default1.aspx?ItemID=310 Republic of Macedonia - Ministry of Foreign Affairs] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110930040551/http://www.mfa.gov.mk/default1.aspx?ItemID=310 |date=2011-09-30 }} Bilateral relations {{en icon}}</ref> Austria maintains an embassy in [[Skopje]], while Macedonia maintains an embassy in [[Vienna]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.embassiesabroad.com/embassies-of/Macedonia |title=Embassies of Macedonia - Vienna |access-date=2010-05-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100108034458/http://www.embassiesabroad.com/embassies-of/Macedonia#2195 |archive-date=2010-01-08 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>

==Relations==
Austria, being a member state of the [[European Union]], supports Macedonia's efforts to join the organization.<ref name=mia/> It also supported Macedonia during the country's visa liberalization process and the [[European Commission|European Commission's]] positive decision in 2009 concerning the start of accession negotiations between the EU and Macedonia.<ref name=mia/>

Austria is one of 131<ref name=bol131>[http://www.emg.rs/en/news/region/144809.html Bolivia is 131. country to use Macedonia's constitutional name] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110123210717/http://www.emg.rs/en/news/region/144809.html |date=2011-01-23 }} Ekonom:east Media Group. ''20-01-2011''</ref> countries recognizing Macedonia by its constitutional name.<ref name=mia/><ref>[http://www.webcitation.org/5nmYdAzYg?url=http://www.europeanfoundation.org/docs/id209.pdf European Foundation] European Foundation Intelligence Digest - Just like old times (Page 4) {{en icon}}</ref><ref>[http://volksgruppen.orf.at/slowenen/aktuell/stories/66625/ Austrian Broadcasting] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110721004236/http://volksgruppen.orf.at/slowenen/aktuell/stories/66625/ |date=July 21, 2011 }} Skopje kalmiert im Namensstreit {{de icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www1.voanews.com/macedonian/news/a-42-2007-07-12-voa2-86465627.html?moddate=2007-07-12 Voice of America - Macedonian] Посета на австрискиот претседател на Скопје {{mk icon}}</ref>

