'''Chouriço doce''' is a [[blood sausage]] prepared with [[pig blood]], [[brown sugar]]<ref name="Júnior"/> or honey,<ref name="TO"/><ref name="Pedroso"/> cashew nuts and spices.<ref name="Júnior"/> Some versions are prepared using almonds.<ref name="TO"/> It has been stated that the dish requires six hours to prepare.<ref name="Júnior"/>
This is a traditional [[Portuguese cuisine|Portuguese]]<ref name="TO"/><ref name="Rodrigues"/> dish from the area of Trás-os-Montes. The dish is served in the Sertão do Seridó communities of [[Rio Grande do Norte]], Brazil as a main dish for a Christmas dinner.<ref name="Júnior"/>
==See also== * [[List of Portuguese dishes]] * [[List of Brazilian sweets and desserts]] * [[List of sausages]]
