{{Infobox dam | name = Dubăsari Dam | name_official = | image = ГЭС Дубоссары двойной кадр.jpg | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Moldova | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = {{coord|47|16|40|N|29|7|25|E|type:landmark_region:MD_source:ruwiki|display=inline,title}} | country = [[Moldova]] | location = [[Dubăsari]] | status = Operational | construction_began = 1951 | opening = 1954 | demolished = | cost = | owner = | dam_type = | dam_length = | dam_height = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | dam_crosses = [[Dniester]] | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = Dubăsari Reservoir | res_capacity_total = | res_catchment = | res_surface = {{convert|67.5|km2|abbr=on}} | res_max_depth = | res_tidal_range = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = 1954 | plant_decommission = | plant_type = | plant_turbines = | plant_capacity = 48&nbsp;MW | plant_annual_gen = | website = | extra = }} The '''Dubăsari Dam''' (also '''''HPP Dubasari''''', {{lang-ro|Hidroelectrocentrala de la Dubăsari}}) is a hydroelectric dam at the [[Dniester|Dniester river]] near [[Dubăsari]] in [[Transnistria]], [[Moldova]]. It was built in 1951–1954. The installed capacity of the [[hydroelectric power station]] is 48&nbsp;MW.<ref name=historical> {{cite book | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=iQGyAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA126 | title = Historical Dictionary of Moldova | series = Historical Dictionaries of Europe | first1 = Andrei | last1 = Brezianu | first2 = Vlad | last2 = Spânu | publisher = [[Scarecrow Press]] | year = 2007 | pages = 126–127 | isbn = 9780810864467}} </ref>
The Dubăsari Dam creates the Dubăsari reservoir ({{lang-ro|Rezervuarul Dubăsari}}). The reservoir is {{convert|128|km}} long and has an average width of {{convert|528|m}}. Water surface area is equal to {{convert|67.5|km2}}.<ref name=historical/>
