{{Taxobox | name = Ethiopian dwarf mongoose | status = LC | status_system = iucn3.1 | status_ref = <ref name=iucn>{{IUCN2008 | assessor =Kingdon, J. | assessor2 =Van Rompaey, J. | assessor3 =Hoffmann, M. | last-assessor-amp =yes| year =2008| title = Helogale hirtula | id = 41608 | downloaded =22 March 2009}} Database entry includes a brief justification of why this species is of least concern</ref> | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordate|Chordata]] | classis = [[Mammal]]ia | ordo = [[Carnivora]] | familia = [[Herpestidae]] | subfamilia = [[Herpestinae]] | genus = ''[[Helogale]]'' | species = '''''H. hirtula''''' | binomial = ''Helogale hirtula'' | binomial_authority = [[Oldfield Thomas|Thomas]], 1904 | range_map = Ethiopian Dwarf Mongoose area.png | range_map_caption = Ethiopian dwarf mongoose range | image = Mangoustes naines orientales .jpg }}The '''Ethiopian dwarf mongoose''' (''Helogale hirtula''), also known as the '''desert dwarf mongoose''' or '''Somali dwarf mongoose''', is a [[mongoose]] found in [[eastern Africa]], particularly [[Ethiopia]], [[Kenya]], and [[Somalia]].
The Ethiopian dwarf mongoose will send out warning calls to its family if a predator is detected. They have also been known to produce general alarm calls when danger is not present. These calls have different pitches which indicate different levels of urgency for the family. A study of dwarf mongoose suggested that they could convey the predator's species, distance and elevation to the family all through alarm calls.<ref name=":0" /> ==Subspecies== *''Helogale hirtula hirtula'' *''Helogale hirtula ahlselli'' *''Helogale hirtula annulata'' *''Helogale hirtula lutescens'' *''Helogale hirtula powelli'' ==References== {{Reflist|refs=<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Collier|first=Katie|last2=Radford|first2=Andrew N.|last3=Townsend|first3=Simon W.|last4=Manser|first4=Marta B.|date=Summer 2017|title=Wild dwarf mongoose produce general alert and predator-specific alarm calls|url=|journal=Behavioral Ecology|volume=28|pages=1293-1301|via=Science Citation Index [SCI] - ISI Web of Knowledge}}</ref> }}
