{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
{{Other uses|Liard (disambiguation)}}

[[File:Liard de France Louis XIV 1655.jpg|thumbnail|right|Liard de France Louis XIV 1655]]

The '''liard''' was a subdivision of the [[Austrian Netherlands kronenthaler|kronenthaler]], the [[currency]] of the [[Austrian Netherlands]] (modern [[Belgium]]). There were 216 liards to a kronenthaler. Following the [[France|French]] occupation of the Austrian Netherlands in 1794, the kronenthaler was replaced by the [[French franc]]. Today, in [[Walloon_language|Walloon]] dialects, '''des liards''' is still a synonym of "money" in general.

The '''liard''' was also a [[France|French]] coin, worth three [[French denier|deniers]], which appeared under [[Louis XIV]] and was the smallest in use in the period prior to the [[French revolution|Revolution]].


