{{Infobox TV channel | name = Sky 3D | logofile = | logosize = | logocaption = | logoalt = | logo2 = | launch = {{Start date and age|2011|9|6|df=y}} | closed date = {{End date and age|2018|1|15|df=y}} | picture format = [[1080i]] ([[3D television|3DTV]]) | share = | share as of = | share source = | network = [[Sky Italia]] | owner = [[Sky Italia]] [[Sky plc]] | slogan = ''La nuova dimensione in televisione'' | country = | language = [[Italian language|Italian]] | broadcast area = [[Italy]] | affiliates = | headquarters = | former names = | replaced names = | replaced by names = | sister names = | timeshift names = | web = {{URL|http://www.sky.it/3d}} | terr serv 1 = | terr chan 1 = | sat serv 1 = [[Sky Italia|Sky]] | sat chan 1 = Channels 150, 209 e 321 }}
'''Sky 3D''' was a [[3D television]] channel on the Sky platform, that launched on 6 September 2011 with the [[film]] [[Winx Club 3D: Magical Adventure]]. The channel broadcasts a mixture of movies, entertainment and sport for 12 hours a day from 01:00 pm to 01:00 am GMT.
==History== On 11 January 2016, Sky 3D modified the logo to conform to the British TV channel of the same name.
From 8 to 16 October 2016 the channel was entirely dedicated to 3D cinema to remember the ancient films of the history of cinema in 3D<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.digital-news.it/news/sky-italia/42649/sky-3d-vintage-un-progetto-editoriale-unico-in-un-canale-senza-precedenti|title=Sky 3D Vintage, un progetto editoriale unico in un canale senza precedenti - Digital-News|date=2016-10-08|work=Digital News|access-date=2018-01-18|language=it-IT}}</ref>.
In December 2017, Sky announced that the channel will only be available [[Video on demand|on demand]] from January 2018. The dedicated Sky 3D TV channel closed on January 15, 2018 and programming will only be available on ''Sky On Demand''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sky.it/assistenza/conosci/servizi-extra/sky-3d.html|title=Assistenza Sky 3D {{!}} Sky|website=www.sky.it|language=it|access-date=2018-01-18}}</ref>.
